<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="261" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24591/3–1546: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-15">March 15,
                                1946</date>.<lb/>[Received March 15—10:29 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>815. Soviet press March 15 publishes Tass denial reading as follows in
                            translation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>There has been published in American press a statement of State
                                    Department of USA that there is taking place in Iran a shifting
                                    of Soviet Military units through Tehran and [toward?] western
                                    frontier of Iran. Tass is authorized to state that this report
                                    absolutely does not correspond to reality.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Sent Department 815, repeated Tehran 62, Tabriz and Frankfurt.</p>
                        <closer>[<signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                            </signed>]</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>